  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "With the ActivityKit framework, you can start a Live Activity to share live updates from your app in the Dynamic Island and on the Lock Screen. Especially for apps that push the limit of notifications to provide updated information, Live Activities can offer a richer, interactive and highly glanceable way for people to keep track of an event or activity over a couple of hours. For example, a sports app might start a Live Activity that makes live information available at a glance for the duration of a game.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A Live Activity appears in highly visible contexts:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "On the Lock Screen of iPhone and iPad, it appears at the top of the list alongside notifications.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "On devices that support it, the Live Activity appears in the Dynamic Island.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "On iPhone in StandBy, it appears using a minimal presentation at the top of the screen or scaled to fill the display.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "On the Home Screen and when other apps are in use, updates appear as a banner at the top of the screen of devices that don’t support the Dynamic Island if the update includes an alert configuration.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "In the Smart Stack in watchOS, the leading and trailing view for the Dynamic Island appear together to form the Live Activity.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10184",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": ", ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10185",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": ", and ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10194",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Related sessions from WWDC23",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In addition to viewing real-time information, people tap a Live Activity to launch your app and interact with its buttons or toggles to perform essential functionality without launching your app. In the Dynamic Island, people touch and hold the compact and minimal presentations to show an expanded presentation with more content that feels like a peek into your app.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "live-activity-dynamic-island",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In your app, use ActivityKit to configure, start, update, and end the Live Activity, and create the user interface of your Live Activities with a widget extension, ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/SwiftUI",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ", and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/WidgetKit",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". As a result of using SwiftUI and WidgetKit, you can share code between widgets and Live Activities or develop them in tandem.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "However, Live Activities use a different mechanism to receive updates compared to widgets. Instead of using a timeline mechanism, Live Activities receive updated data from your app with ActivityKit and remotely with ActivityKit push notifications. Starting with iOS 17.2 and iPadOS 17.2, you can also start Live Activities with ActivityKit push notifications.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "visionOS doesn’t load WidgetKit extensions found in compatible iPad and iPhone apps. As a result, it doesn’t support Live Activities.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
